            <p>Rev Dr S Morais<lb/>
                546 N 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi><lb/>
                Philad<hi rend="sup">a</hi><lb/>
                Penna<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>8&#47;8&#47;87.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I have written Dr Drachman to search the Zeitgeist&#58;&#45;<lb/> I have written Max Cohen to search the first numbers of the Amer.<lb/> Isra.  I will search the Reformer and say the last 10 years<lb/> of the American Isra. &#40;I mean the Reformer of Dr. Kohler&#44; and the<lb/> older Reformer&#41;.  If you and your son could look up Amer. Isra.<lb/> for say 1867&#45;1877 we should gain by dividing the work.  <hi rend="underline">Dates must be</hi><lb/> noted.  My idea is to find proofs of favoring no circumcision&#44; no restoration&#44;<lb/> no dietary laws&#44; no origin of Torah &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; or transfer of Sabbath from the<lb/> writings of Wise&#44; Moses &#40;which Moses is teacher at Cincinnati&#63;&#41; Kohler&#44; Sonneschein<lb/> Hirsch  E and others of that ilk who have been on Board of Governors or executive<lb/> the Occident may aid us.  Is it true the Restoration question was not agitated<lb/> or mooted before the union of American Hebrew Congregations was<lb/> started&#63;  I shall leave for New York Thursday evening&#45;&#45;<lb/> with regards yrs H. Pereira Mendes<lb/> 297 Broadway Newport R. I.<lb/></p>
            </body>
